      • setEnabledProtocols

        public void setEnabledProtocols(String enabledProtocols)
        Sets the list of protocols that are enabled for use by SSL connections.

        The specified protocols must be among SSLv2Hello, SSLv3, TLSv1, TLSv1.1 and TLSv1.2; otherwise, applying this configuration over an SSLSocket later would fail.

        Defaults to TLSv1,TLSv1.1,TLSv1.2.

        Parameters:
        enabledProtocols - comma separated list of protocols enabled to use by SSL connections; must not be null or empty.
